										<h1>Design Options</h1>
									</header>
									<span class="image main"><img src="images/pic11.jpg" alt="Design Options" /></span>
									
									<p>Through AI-assisted design exploration, three distinct approaches were developed to address the challenges identified in Montefiore Square. Each option represents a different philosophy toward public space transformation, ranging from conservative improvements to comprehensive redesign.</p>
									
									<hr class="major" />
									
									<h2>Option 1: Minimal Intervention</h2>
									<div class="row">
										<div class="col-6 col-12-medium">
											<span class="image fit"><img src="images/pic01.jpg" alt="Minimal Intervention Concept" /></span>
										</div>
										<div class="col-6 col-12-medium">
											<h3>Concept Overview</h3>
											<p>This approach focuses on cost-effective improvements that can be implemented quickly without major construction. It prioritizes immediate user comfort and safety enhancements.</p>
											
											<h4>Key Features:</h4>
											<ul>
												<li>Strategic placement of movable seating</li>
												<li>Temporary shade structures (umbrellas/canopies)</li>
												<li>Improved lighting fixtures</li>
												<li>Wayfinding signage</li>
												<li>Planters with seasonal flowers</li>
											</ul>
											
											<h4>Pros:</h4>
											<ul>
												<li>Low cost</li>
												<li>Quick implementation</li>
												<li>Flexibility for future changes</li>
											</ul>
											
											<h4>Cons:</h4>
											<ul>
												<li>Limited long-term impact</li>
												<li>No permanent shade or greenery</li>
												<li>Doesn't address accessibility issues</li>
											</ul>
										</div>
									</div>
									
									<hr class="major" />
									
									<h2>Option 2: Balanced Redesign</h2>
									<div class="row">
										<div class="col-6 col-12-medium">
											<span class="image fit"><img src="images/pic02.jpg" alt="Balanced Redesign Concept" /></span>
										</div>
										<div class="col-6 col-12-medium">
											<h3>Concept Overview</h3>
											<p>This middle-ground approach combines permanent infrastructure improvements with flexible programming spaces. It balances immediate needs with long-term community benefits.</p>
											
											<h4>Key Features:</h4>
											<ul>
												<li>Permanent shade structures with solar panels</li>
												<li>Integrated seating walls and benches</li>
												<li>Native tree planting for natural shade</li>
												<li>Pervious paving for stormwater management</li>
												<li>Flexible event space</li>
												<li>Improved lighting and safety features</li>
											</ul>
											
											<h4>Pros:</h4>
											<ul>
												<li>Addresses multiple user needs</li>
												<li>Sustainable design features</li>
												<li>Moderate cost with high impact</li>
												<li>Phased implementation possible</li>
											</ul>
											
											<h4>Cons:</h4>
											<ul>
												<li>Requires more funding than minimal option</li>
												<li>Construction disruption</li>
												<li>Maintenance commitments</li>
											</ul>
										</div>
									</div>
									
									<hr class="major" />
									
									<h2>Option 3: Bold Transformation</h2>
									<div class="row">
										<div class="col-6 col-12-medium">
											<span class="image fit"><img src="images/pic03.jpg" alt="Bold Transformation Concept" /></span>
										</div>
										<div class="col-6 col-12-medium">
											<h3>Concept Overview</h3>
											<p>This comprehensive redesign reimagines the plaza as a signature public space for Harlem. It incorporates ambitious programming, sustainable infrastructure, and iconic design elements.</p>
											
											<h4>Key Features:</h4>
											<ul>
												<li>Integrated amphitheater for performances</li>
												<li>Community garden and urban farm</li>
												<li>Interactive water feature</li>
												<li>Public art installations</li>
												<li>Underground stormwater retention</li>
												<li>Smart lighting and WiFi infrastructure</li>
												<li>Year-round programming capabilities</li>
											</ul>
											
											<h4>Pros:</h4>
											<ul>
												<li>Maximum community benefit</li>
												<li>Tourist destination potential</li>
												<li>Comprehensive sustainability</li>
												<li>Legacy project for Harlem</li>
											</ul>
											
											<h4>Cons:</h4>
											<ul>
												<li>High capital cost</li>
												<li>Long implementation timeline</li>
												<li>Complex maintenance requirements</li>
												<li>Potential community resistance to change</li>
											</ul>
										</div>
									</div>
									
